Get predicted data from fitted GAMs across period of observation

anlz_prd.Rd

Get predicted data from fitted GAMs across period of observation

anlz_prd(moddat = NULL, mods = NULL, ...)

Arguments

moddat

input raw data, one station and parameter
mods

optional list of model objects
...

additional arguments passed to other methods

Value

a data.frame with predictions

See also

Other analyze: anlz_avgseason(), anlz_backtrans(), anlz_fit(), anlz_gam(), anlz_perchg(), anlz_prdday(), anlz_smooth(), anlz_trans(), anlz_trndseason()

Examples

library(dplyr)

# get predictions for all four gams
tomod <- rawdat %>%
  filter(station %in% 32) %>%
  filter(param %in% 'chl')
if (FALSE) {
anlz_prd(tomod, trans = 'log10')
}
# use previously fitted list of models
trans <- 'log10'
mods <- list(
  gam0 = anlz_gam(tomod, mod = 'gam0', trans = trans),
  gam1 = anlz_gam(tomod, mod = 'gam1', trans = trans), 
  gam2 = anlz_gam(tomod, mod = 'gam2', trans = trans)
  )
anlz_prd(mods = mods)
